      Fat finger
   =20
 =20
I don=E2=80=99t understand this story but maybe you do?A Rancho Cordova gas=
 station manager who accidentally set his pumps at just 69 cents a gallon i=
s speaking out after being fired.=E2=80=9CWell, it was a mistake that I did=
, you know,=E2=80=9D said former gas station manager John Szczecina.Szczeci=
na accidentally put a decimal in the wrong spot and began selling the $6.99=
 gas for just 69 cents. It cost the gas station $16,000 and it cost Szczeci=
na his job.=E2=80=9CAnd I thought, =E2=80=98this is a nightmare,=E2=80=99=
=E2=80=9D Szczecina said. =E2=80=9CI put all three prices on there except t=
he diesel, but the last one kind of didn=E2=80=99t go, you know, right.=E2=
=80=9DPeople started posting the low price on social media and calling frie=
nds and family. The lines formed fast to guzzle it up.That=E2=80=99s like 2=
,500 gallons of mispriced gas? That=E2=80=99s like 200 Honda Civics?=C2=A0L=
ike =E2=80=A6=C2=A0there you are, managing your gas station, and you see th=
e huge line of cars, and you are like =E2=80=9Chuh that=E2=80=99s odd,=E2=
=80=9D and you maybe go out to the 20th person in line and say =E2=80=9Chey=
 buddy, why are you waiting on this long line for my gas,=E2=80=9D and he s=
ays =E2=80=9Cit=E2=80=99s so cheap=E2=80=9D and you look at the sign and sa=
y =E2=80=9Coops=E2=80=9D and change it? Like I get that sometimes traders i=
n high-speed electronic markets can accidentally do millions of dollars of =
mispriced trades in a second before they realize it, but the gas gets pumpe=
d one gallon at a time, you know?
